        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued March 28 at 3:13AM CDT by NWS Brownsville TX</headline>
        <description>At 313 AM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Villa Verde, or over Progreso, moving northeast at 25 mph.

HAZARD...Half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Minor hail damage to vegetation is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Progreso City Offices, Weslaco High School, Villa Verde, Mercedes,
Weslaco Mid Valley Airport, Black Elementary School, Mercedes Junior
High School, Midway South, Weslaco City Park, and Llano Grande
Country Club.

This includes US Highway 281 between mile markers 802 and 806.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
